				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ H\left({SNP}_1,\dots, {SNP}_k\right)=-\sum \limits_{snp_1=0}^2\dots \sum \limits_{snp_k=0}^2p\left({snp}_1,\dots, {snp}_k\right)\log p\left({snp}_1,\dots, {snp}_k\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M10" display="block"><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=",,"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">SNP</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>…</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">SNP</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:munderover><mml:mo movablelimits="false">∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">snp</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:munderover><mml:mo>…</mml:mo><mml:munderover><mml:mo movablelimits="false">∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">snp</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:munderover><mml:mi>p</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=",,"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">snp</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>…</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">snp</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>log</mml:mo><mml:mi>p</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=",,"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">snp</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>…</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">snp</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2019_3022_Article_Equ5.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
        <p id="Par54">On the basis of binary expression of genotype data, we can conduct the logic <bold>AND</bold> operation to calculate the mutual information efficiently. For example, we use Eq.(<xref rid="Equ6" ref-type="">6</xref>) to calculate <italic>I</italic>(<italic>Class</italic> |<italic>SNP</italic><sub><italic>B</italic></sub>, <italic>SNP</italic><sub><italic>C</italic></sub>) shown in <italic>M</italic><sub><italic>bit</italic></sub>.
<disp-formula id="Equ6"><label>6</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M11">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
